The Senior Special Assistant to President Muhammadu Buhari on Niger Delta Affairs, Senator Ita Enang has become the first aspirant to purchase the 2023 governorship form in Akwa Ibom State under the platform of the All Progressives Congress, APC The APC had on Tuesday, April 26, 2022, begun the sale of Expression of Interest and Nomination forms for aspirants seeking various elective positions in the forthcoming elections. Enang who spoke shortly after purchasing the forms at the rate of N50 million( Expression of interest- N10m, Governorship Nomination form -N40M) said there is no division in the Akwa Ibom APC. The Presidential Aide explained that what looked like fracas or factions in the Party have been handled adding that whatever was remaining as little misunderstanding will be properly settled before the nomination exercise next month. “There is no more faction in Akwa Ibom State APC. All interests have been sunk into one family and the family is under the leadership of President Muhammadu Buhari and the National Chairman. Whatever is remaining, we will tidy up before we go into nomination. We are going into nomination as one united family; in one venue, coming up with one candidate and one winner for Gubernatorial, Senatorial, House of Representatives and House of Assembly elections.” He also noted that he would change the mode of governance in the state where accountability will be the order of the day especially the way funds are generated from the state to the national level as well as ensuring a cordial relationship with the federal government to bring development to the state.